rega'??</span><hr size=1> Hi Dottie – thanks for your help!<br><br>The good news is, I’m actually learning Italian at the moment <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> … the BAD news is I’m still very much a beginner!<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Anyway, I think I’ll follow your lead and try to find some of these Italian websites.  Sometimes, non-English language sites have buttons you can click for an English translation, and it’s also always worth checking out their ‘links’ pages for links to related English language sites.<br><br>I know there are also free translation sites online (such as “Babelfish”), however they lack the human touch and the results can sometimes be, erm … bizarre!<br><br>Anyway … thanks Dottie: my search feels less lonely now! <br><br>Paul<br>Powys/ UK <br><br>PS – anyone else out there who’s heard of Sara Compton, loves doing research or speaks fluent Italian (unlike me) ??<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/udotzap.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DOTZAP</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://members.aol.com/maidenntheshaden/btrfly6.gif height=35 width=35 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Angelight</span><br>  Posts: 3004<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/21/01 1:21:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesfrm51.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=362.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/maidenntheshaden/maxmouse.jpg WIDT